The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bhaichung all geared up
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Bhaichung all geared up
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: India skipper Bhaichung Bhutia is all geared up to rub shoulders with the likes of Kaka, Frank Lampard, Steven Gerrard and Didier Drogba on the eve of the prestigious Goal4africa charity match to commemorate Nelson Mandelas 90th birthday in Munich.         
	Watching him from the stands will be his wife Madhuri and mentor Karma Bhutia.         
	A few of my Indian team colleagues in Portugal have given me their jerseys to get it autographed by some star players, Bhutia said.         
	Inspired by the fundraisers main objective, to create better education for the children of Africa, the two teams are called Edu and Cation.                                                                                                                          
